result.execSummary:
The defendant Amalia Marie Kutschera was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Psilocin/Psilocybin, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars except in direct furtherance of employment as a disc jockey, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Defendant is prohibited from being in possession of any chemical compounds that are capable of creating a hallucinogenic effect.
Defendant to comply with any further conditions, counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 1:04 p.m. Defendant Amalia Marie Kutschera in court with attorney David Paul Frank Templeton.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Upon motion of the State the Court amends Ct 1 to Misdemeanor Possession of Psilocybin/Psilocin contrary to Wis Stat 961.41(3g)(d).  Plea: Cts 1 & 2 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Atty Templeton. Statement by DE. Court orders: S/W 18 mos Probation - Conditions: AODA and follow through, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars except in direct furtherance of employment as a disc jockey, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, No possession of any chemical compounds that are capable of creating a hallucinogenic effect, any other terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by supervising agent, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. Appeal rights given.
